    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start": "00:08:07,392",
      "end": "00:08:12,798",
      "start_seconds": 487.392,
      "end_seconds": 492.798,
      "text": "What do you like to do in your free time?",
      "audio_path": "audio/how_en_121.wav"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start": "00:08:13,118",
      "end": "00:08:17,383",
      "start_seconds": 493.118,
      "end_seconds": 497.383,
      "text": "I like to cook and exercise.",
      "audio_path": "audio/how_en_122.wav"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start": "00:08:17,403",
      "end": "00:08:18,584",
      "start_seconds": 497.403,
      "end_seconds": 498.584,
      "text": "Sounds good.",
      "audio_path": "audio/how_en_123.wav"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start": "00:08:18,604",
      "end": "00:08:21,087",
      "start_seconds": 498.604,
      "end_seconds": 501.087,
      "text": "Can you tell me if you are learning English now?",
      "audio_path": "audio/how_en_124.wav"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start": "00:08:22,906",
      "end": "00:08:31,878",
      "start_seconds": 502.906,
      "end_seconds": 511.878,
      "text": "I think that you got it, that I'm learning English right now.",
      "audio_path": "audio/how_en_125.wav"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start": "00:08:31,898",
      "end": "00:08:32,318",
      "start_seconds": 511.898,
      "end_seconds": 512.318,
      "text": "Absolutely.",
      "audio_path": "audio/how_en_126.wav"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start": "00:08:32,338",
      "end": "00:08:33,740",
      "start_seconds": 512.338,
      "end_seconds": 513.74,
      "text": "I just wanted to hear you say it.",
      "audio_path": "audio/how_en_127.wav"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start": "00:08:33,760",
      "end": "00:08:36,123",
      "start_seconds": 513.76,
      "end_seconds": 516.123,
      "text": "You're doing great.",
      "audio_path": "audio/how_en_128.wav"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start": "00:08:36,143",
      "end": "00:08:36,363",
      "start_seconds": 516.143,
      "end_seconds": 516.363,
      "text": "Keep it up.",
      "audio_path": "audio/how_en_129.wav"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start": "00:08:36,383",
      "end": "00:08:36,724",
      "start_seconds": 516.383,
      "end_seconds": 516.724,
      "text": "Here.",
      "audio_path": "audio/how_en_130.wav"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start": "00:08:36,924",
      "end": "00:08:38,827",
      "start_seconds": 516.924,
      "end_seconds": 518.827,
      "text": "This is roughly how it happens.",
      "audio_path": "audio/how_en_131.wav"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start": "00:08:39,267",
      "end": "00:08:51,563",
      "start_seconds": 519.267,
      "end_seconds": 531.563,
      "text": "Look, if at some point it says something incorrectly, you can just give it a clarification regarding that, or ask it to break down the questions one by one, because sometimes it can give them out as a whole list.",
      "audio_path": "audio/how_en_132.wav"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start": "00:08:52,387",
      "end": "00:09:05,469",
      "start_seconds": 532.387,
      "end_seconds": 545.469,
      "text": "But overall, look, the conversation is built coolly, you can also ask it, for example, to translate each question or to note any mistakes you make when you answer, so use it.",
      "audio_path": "audio/how_en_133.wav"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start": "00:09:05,489",
      "end": "00:09:16,167",
      "start_seconds": 545.489,
      "end_seconds": 556.167,
      "text": "And after that, we will practice writing, yes, you heard that right, I always tell everyone, the more you write, the better you speak, so here's a prompt for writing.",
      "audio_path": "audio/how_en_134.wav"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start": "00:09:17,800",
      "end": "00:09:47,227",
      "start_seconds": 557.8,
      "end_seconds": 587.227,
      "text": "Help me write three simple sentences about myself in English for A1 level. Now I will show you what it replied, so look, I'm adding. First, it wrote me templates that I can use. And then it gives \"your turn\" type of prompt, meaning for you to write these three sentences to it. In this case, when you write your sentences to it, it will correct you if something is wrong, or conversely, praise you if you wrote everything correctly. And now a very important nuance.",
      "audio_path": "audio/how_en_135.wav"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start": "00:09:47,547",
      "end": "00:09:51,791",
      "start_seconds": 587.547,
      "end_seconds": 591.791,
      "text": "After each session, you need to record your progress.",
      "audio_path": "audio/how_en_136.wav"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start": "00:09:51,871",
      "end": "00:09:57,918",
      "start_seconds": 591.871,
      "end_seconds": 597.918,
      "text": "You need to help this machine record everything you write to it.",
      "audio_path": "audio/how_en_137.wav"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start": "00:09:57,958",
      "end": "00:10:00,780",
      "start_seconds": 597.958,
      "end_seconds": 600.78,
      "text": "Also a prompt.",
      "audio_path": "audio/how_en_138.wav"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start": "00:10:00,800",
      "end": "00:10:07,327",
      "start_seconds": 600.8,
      "end_seconds": 607.327,
      "text": "Make a short summary of the lesson we covered, what mistakes are repeated, to review next time.",
      "audio_path": "audio/how_en_139.wav"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start": "00:10:08,008",
      "end": "00:10:09,489",
      "start_seconds": 608.008,
      "end_seconds": 609.489,
      "text": "No more than 100 words.",
      "audio_path": "audio/how_en_140.wav"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start": "00:10:09,509",
      "end": "00:10:21,877",
      "start_seconds": 609.509,
      "end_seconds": 621.877,
      "text": "Look, you can insert all of this both at the end of this lesson and at the beginning of the next, so that you don't forget what you've already covered and can pay attention to what you need to work on more.",
      "audio_path": "audio/how_en_141.wav"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start": "00:10:22,117",
      "end": "00:10:24,642",
      "start_seconds": 622.117,
      "end_seconds": 624.642,
      "text": "And now there will probably be a very logical question from you.",
      "audio_path": "audio/how_en_142.wav"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start": "00:10:24,742",
      "end": "00:10:27,747",
      "start_seconds": 624.742,
      "end_seconds": 627.747,
      "text": "Okay, I practiced today, what should I do next?",
      "audio_path": "audio/how_en_143.wav"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start": "00:10:27,807",
      "end": "00:10:30,653",
      "start_seconds": 627.807,
      "end_seconds": 630.653,
      "text": "How to do all this independently?",
      "audio_path": "audio/how_en_144.wav"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start": "00:10:30,773",
      "end": "00:10:35,361",
      "start_seconds": 630.773,
      "end_seconds": 635.361,
      "text": "And I'll tell you, you don't need to reinvent the wheel, because I've already invented it for you.",
      "audio_path": "audio/how_en_145.wav"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start": "00:10:36,067",
      "end": "00:10:41,835",
      "start_seconds": 636.067,
      "end_seconds": 641.835,
      "text": "You just need to copy this prompt and then follow our already created roadmap.",
      "audio_path": "audio/how_en_146.wav"
    },
    {
